  "market_context": "Hourly displacement up confirmed on 1H chart (close at 3843.50), followed by a sweep of a prior low on the 15-second chart. The 5-minute chart showed failure to close below that low, indicating potential re-entry into the range during NY session.",
  "key_observation": "An aggressive low sweep on the 15-second chart after an hourly displacement, combined with a 5-minute failure to displace below the low, created a high-probability OTE zone on the 1-minute for a long entry targeting previous highs (~4R).",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the hourly displacement move upward on the 1H chart (close at 3843.50) establishing bullish bias and structure.",
    "Step 2: Drop to the 5-minute chart and observe a sequence of down-close candles followed by a green candle at 10:00 that failed to close below the prior swing low, signaling potential rejection.",
    "Step 3: Zoom to the 15-second chart to confirm an aggressive sweep of that same low (reaching 3807.75) with a strong wick and immediate reversal back into the range.",
    "Step 4: Locate the OTE zone on the 1-minute chart using Fibonacci retracement (0.62–0.79 levels) aligned with the PD Array (3841.25–3867.25) and the slash-down closed candle as the entry trigger.",
    "Step 5: Place stop below the swept low (3807.75) and target previous highs for ~4R reward, noting price reached those levels."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade achieved over 4R profit by reaching previous highs before exit.",
  "lessons": "Aggressive liquidity sweeps followed by failure to displace on a higher timeframe (5-min) validate OTE entries on lower timeframes (1-min/15-sec); always require HTF structure + LTF confirmation + POI alignment.",
